node.text:
⚠ READ THIS: ⚠

MONEY doesn't buy happiness. You can have money and still feel miserable.
Maybe because of the stress that comes with running a business, maybe because you have less free time, there are many possible reasons...

BUT....

...you'll never see a poor person who struggles to buy food "live a happy life". Not having money doesn't buy happiness either. Worrying about tomorrow because your'e financially unstable doesn't make you happy. Living paycheck to paycheck isn't the definition of happiness.

It's all about balance. Money buys time and freedom if earned correctly. It's having time for everything & having the freedom to do whatever you want whenever you want that brings happiness into your life and BOTH, time & freedom have a price tag. That's why I'm chasing the money.

You can't be broke & free.
You can be rich & free, therefore let's get that money.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
⚠READ THIS!!!!⚠

Shoes, chains, fancy brands....
all about the image.

FANCY SH*T showed off to the public has nothing to do with success,
it has EVERYTHING to do with personal branding.

SO MANY kids are buying expensive sh*t and waste their money "because rapper "x" does so it must be cool & I need it too".

Public figures use luxury brands as ASSETS.
For CREDIBILITY. IMAGE. BRANDING.
All of those 3 increase their popularity,
hype & lastly - SALES.

(Truly rich people wear luxury brands too but they don't feel the urge to flex it to everyone. You barely see anyone flexing a yacht on IG. Why? Because rich people don't give a f*ck about likes & followers, they just live their life in peace and silence.)

Average people use luxury brands as LIABILITIES.
You're not a f*cking rap artist, you don't need that
bling. You don't have to show cars and money,
someone who's building his image by rapping
about money and cars DOES.

Your favorite rapstar spends money on luxuries
to make more money, you spend money on
luxuries to look cool & be broke.

Think about it and change the way you think.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
STOP OVERTHINKING!
STOP BEING AFRAID!

While TONS and TONS of people got depressed, lost their jobs, ended up in isolation while the economy was shut down, this guy saw an OPPORTUNITY!

I don't usually post "niche content" on this page, but this post is 100% RELEVANT and should be an eye-opener.

No rich kid,
No marketing MBA genius,
No revolutionary idea,

Khaby simply did it.
He just started taking action.
He surely didn't plan to "Become rich in 2 years".
Quit your BS and simply take action.

Don't expect results,
just hustle, just put in the work,
everything else will follow.

TRUST. THE. PROCESS.
..or remain the same.
.
.
.
.
.
